data.reddit:
Out of no where, I have these random attacks where my lungs will just not “fill up all the way”? If that makes sense. I can’t complete a yawn, deep breaths do not suffice; my heart starts racing, I get dizzy, and damn near pass out. I fainted because of it the other day and it’s really starting to freak me out. I could physically feel that I wasn’t getting enough oxygen to my brain. I do not have a URI, my chest X-ray was clear, I was given an Albuterol inhaler which does nothing for the breathing but only worsens the fast heart rate, which triggers my anxiety, and makes my breathing situation worse. From what I’ve tried so far, Klonopin has been the only remedy to this issue.. I am almost never anxious during these ‘attacks’ so I don’t see it being an anxiety trigger - especially since I’ve had anxiety for a while now, and this has never happened. 


tldr; It’s just a sudden rush of adrenaline, even my hands can start shaking, my heart starts racing, pounding, my chest gets tight, and sore and I cannot breathe so much so that I get dizzy and feel as though I’m going to faint. Klonopin tends to help.

I don’t know if this helps, but from my lab work, my granulocyte and leukocyte counts were both a bit high, my mean platelet was a bit low. And I recently removed the Nexplanon implant after having it for about 5 years

Age: 21
Sex: female
Height: 5’3
Weight: 260
Race: mixed 
Duration of complaint: 2-3 weeks
Location (Geographic and on body): chest/lungs
Any existing relevant medical issues (if any)
Current medications (if any): Klonopin (as needed)
